''This article is about the Belgian singer.  For the Kira responsible for "Wenn du den Himmel nicht aufmachst", see [[Kira (German singer)]].''

'''Kira''' (born '''Natasja de Witte''', [[3 May]] [[1977]], [[Affligem]], [[Belgium]]) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[singer]] and [[model (person)|model]].

==History==
Kira was born in Affligem, where she has lived her whole life.<ref>http://www.kira-music.com Kira's web site, retrieved on September 30, 2007.  Note:  This link is now dead.  It is only partially available via archive.org; see, for example, http://web.archive.org/web/20070606083234/www.kira-music.com/front1024.htm, retrieved July 21, 2009.</ref>  

At the age of thirteen Kira had her first brush with fame when she appeared on the Belgian [[television|TV]] show ''[[Stars in Their Eyes]]''.  In 2000 she competed in the Belgian version of ''[[Popstars]]'' and was voted in the top ten.  That same year she was runner-up in the Miss Belgium beauty contest.<ref>http://www.geocities.net/natasjadewitte/index.html Retrieved September 30, 2007.  Note:  This link is now dead, but Kira's involvement in these events is also mentioned on http://www.dancevibes.be/artists/kira-biography-discography/ , retrieved July 21, 2009.</ref>

In March 2002 Kira was introduced to [[record producer]]s Bart Grinaert and the brothers Bert and Maarten Wilmaers, who are known for producing the Viper records ''The Twister'' and ''Blue Sunshine'' and Montini Experience's ''My House is Your House'', and [[remix]]ed versions of songs such as [[Sash!]]'s "Mysterious Times" and Groovezone's "Eisbaer".  The first result of this collaboration was Kira's debut single "I'll Be Your Angel", for which she was signed worldwide (except Benelux) to BMG NuLife Records in May 2002.<ref>http://www.dancevibes.be/artists/kira.jsp Dancevibes.be, retrieved September 30, 2007.</ref>  The [[single (music)|single]] went to #15 in the Belgian [[record chart|chart]] and #9 in the [[UK Single Chart]], leading to her live performance of the song on [[BBC TV]]'s ''[[Top of the Pops]]'', where she was on stage next to [[Moloko]] and [[Sting (musician)|Sting]].  It was also released in the [[United States]], [[Spain]] and [[Australia]].<ref>http://www.kira-music.com Kira's web site.  Note:  As noted above, this link is now dead.</ref>

==Discography==
* "I'll Be Your Angel" (2003)
* "2 Hearts" (2003)
* "All My Life" (2003)

